==English==

===Etymology===
From a regional use<ref>{{R:Duden|Stein}}</ref> of {{der|en|de|Stein||stone}}. Probably a clipping of {{m|de|Steingut||stoneware}} or {{m|de|Steinkrug||stone pitcher}}. Compare {{cog|ang|stǣna||stone jug, a pot of stone or earth}}. More at {{m|en|stean}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/staɪn/|lang=en}}
*: {{rhymes|aɪn|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[beer]] [[mug]], usually made of [[ceramic]].
#* {{RQ:Frgsn Zlnstn|IV}}
#*: So this was my future home, I thought! Certainly it made a brave picture. I had seen similar ones fired-in on many a Heidelberg '''stein'''. Backed by towering hills,{{...}}a sky of palest Gobelin flecked with fat, fleecy little clouds, it in truth looked a dear little city; the city of one's dreams.
#* '''1974''', {{w|Thomas Pynchon}}, ''{{w|Gravity's Rainbow}}''
